added.title: Mayhem in Mascot
added.description: After their attempt to get a photo with every storefront mascot is foiled, Ben and Gwen sneak out at night to get their photo with the wooden bear totem known as "Yawk", only to find he and the other mascots have come to life!

added.title: Bomzobo Lives
added.description: During a routine trip to the DMV, Max takes a driving test to renew his license, but when a disguised Zombozo hijacks the role of instructor, Ben goes alien to stop the baddie and save their family road trip.

added.title: Animorphosis
added.description: As the Tennyson trio dig up dinosaur fossils in the Badlands, Ben is unaware that Vilgax and Dr. Amino have teamed up to steal alien DNA from within the Omnitrix, but once extracted, Vilgax double crosses his fellow villain. Ben must now join forces with the evil doctor to have a chance to defeat the big baddie, but can Dr. Amino be trusted?

added.title: The 11th Alien Part 2
added.description: After discovering that Vilgax has joined forces with the Weatherheads to trick him into turning over the Omnitrix, Ben must not only overcome his doubts, but fully embrace his new powers if he is to beat his foes.

added.title: Fear the Fogg
added.description: As Max attempts to get Ben and Gwen to the Four Corners Monument before sunset, an ominous fog bank engulfs the roadway and forces Max to drive at a snails pace, but once The Fogg comes to life and attacks the Rust Bucket, Team Tennyson must work together if they are to navigate to safety.

added.title: XLR8 AW2: Speed Round
added.description: The Kinecelerans live life at the fastest pace possible, even when they're letting off steam— hence their supercharged take on what we Earthlings call hockey, where every point is more electrifying than the last!

added.title: Four Arms AW2: The Warspear
added.description: A look at the perilous lengths to which the Tetramands must go in order to forge their formidable Warspears— the weapons that allow them to survive in such a savage wilderness.

added.title: Cannonbolt AW2: When Mega-Sharks Attack!
added.description: Arburia is well-known across the galaxy for its beach season but this year's interplanetary vacationers won't be catching many waves if the Pelarotas can't rid their waters of an unwanted visitor: the Carcharadon, a billion-toothed beast that makes Jaws look like canned tuna!

added.title: Wildvine AW2: The Worldtree
added.description: The Verda World Tree gives life to the entire ecosystem surrounding it, but like any organic matter, this magnificent specimen has a life cycle of its own. That's where the Florauna come in, herding wild Mushroars, gigantic pollen beetles, to fertilize the wilting tree in time for a blooming spring.

added.title: Heatblast AW1: Extreme Season
added.description: At its molten core, Pyros is your typical planet-like star and home to the Pyronites. With rocky exteriors capable of handling these extreme conditions, observe our fiery friends as they pass the time by perfecting their pyrokinetic powers while hanging ten on the gnarliest rivers of lava.

added.title: Four Arms AW1: The Overlordess Games
added.description: Survival is reserved for only the strongest of warriors on Khoros, where Tetramands prove their worth by staving off savage beasts of the wild and going head-to-head inside massive gladiatorial arenas.

added.title: XLR8 AW1: Gauntlet of Gliders
added.description: Kinet, a planet dominated by electrical storms, is home to the lightning quick Kinecelerans! To combat the inclement weather, younglings must complete the Running of the Gauntlet, a most epic retrieval of the gliders worn on their feet. Traversing the desolate terrain at high speeds to reach the lair of a Kinet Molluscarx, the young ones must obtain the creature's precious pearl if they are to fulfill this Kineceleran rite of passage.

added.title: Stinkfly AW1: The Silent Circle
added.description: The circle of life on Lepidopterra is a stinky yet harmonious effort for Lepidopterrans. The wildlife - with slime and toxic gas at their disposal - work together to maintain order on the bustling swamp planet.

added.title: The Park
added.description: The Bears spend a day at the park. Grizz works out. Panda attempts to sell his artwork. Ice Bear trains some kids.

added.title: I Am Ice Bear
added.description: After Ice Bear hits his head, Grizz and Panda notice him acting like a different person.

added.title: Baby Bears Can't Jump
added.description: In order to win a pizza, the Baby Bears play basketball against a ragtag gang of kids.

added.title: Too Many Treasures
added.description: Hoping to fix their fort, Craig enlists the 10 Speeds to give them a ride to the legendary Junk Pile.

added.title: Monster Chef
added.description: Axl and Chef Éclair must enter a cooking contest to try to keep Jestro from getting the hottest chili recipe in the realm.

added.title: Fright Knight
added.description: The Knights explore a strange forest looking for a Book when Jesto unleashes the Book of Fear on them and a new monster, Whiparella, uses her minions to induce the Knights' worst knightmares.

added.title: Seasons Change
added.description: When our heroes return from time off, KO is horrified to discover that things have changed.

added.title: No More Pow Cards
added.description: When KO realizes Pow Cards exclude his friend, he's at a loss of what to do.

added.title: Let's Have a Stakeout
added.description: KO joins Mr. Gar on a stakeout.

added.title: Back in Red Action
added.description: Enid teams up with Red Action to take on a menace from the future.

added.title: Mystery Science Fair 201X
added.description: KO helps Dendy with her science fair project.

added.title: Lad & Logic
added.description: KO learns the story of how Mr. Logic came to the plaza.

added.title: Sparkle Matter Matters
added.description: Unikitty learns that boring, old Richard has never produced any happy Sparkle Matter ever, she cooks up a formula with Dr. Fox that will overload him with emotions! Now, he's making so much Sparkle Matter it's threatening to destroy the kingdom! Can Unikitty help Richard find emotional balance before all is lost?

added.title: Kaiju Kitty
added.description: When a giant monster attacks the Unikingdom, the gang fights back with Dr. Fox's awesome new secret weapon: a massive mega robot! But after the threat is contained, Unikitty doesn't want to stop using the  awesome robot, so she finds excuses for them to use it for everything, no matter how pointless. But what if the greatest threat to the kingdom turns out to be them?

added.title: Rock Friend
added.description: Unikitty discovers Puppycorn's only other friend is a boring old rock. Encouraged to "make more friends," Puppycorn just can't find someone he clicks with, until he takes her advice and decides to literally make a new friend out of the best parts of his friends. This won't go well.

added.title: Hide N' Seek
added.description: Unikitty is proud to be the reigning champ of Hide N' Seek Day. But when Unikitty finds everyone in the kingdom except for Richard, she hunts him down at all costs. Will Richard continue to elude the Princess at her favorite game, and if so, how?!

added.title: Kitty Court
added.description: When Unikitty has a little auto incident with Master Frown, he insists on taking it to court! Frown's thrilled. There's nothing worse than boring old court and he can't wait to subject Unikitty to it! Unikitty is happy to make things right but the trial will be in Unikitty Court, which is so nonsensical and fun. It's Frown's worst nightmare! Will Master Frown succeed in bumming Unikitty out? Or will he be the one punished by their legal antics?

added.title: Too Many Unikittys
added.description: Unikitty comes to the conclusion that everyone would be a lot happier if they would just think the way she does, and with Dr. Fox's help, maybe they can! Unikitty copies her brainwaves into all her friends and turns them Unikitty-fied, so everyone can always be positive! But soon Unikitty quickly realizes there can be too much of a good Princess!

added.title: R & Arr
added.description: It's Lazy Sunday, and Unikitty and Puppycorn are having such an amazing time hanging out on the couch, they never want to move! Richard insists they have chores to do, but they're unwilling to let Lazy Sunday end. The two go to ridiculous lengths to never leave the comfort of their sofa, rowing it across the castle and like a ship and conscripting their friends to abandon their chores and join Lazy Sunday… no matter how dangerous and impossible it might become!

added.title: Letters to Lars
added.description: Steven writes about the latest news of Beach City.

added.title: Heatblast AW2: Cold Snap
added.description: Join the Pyronites as they ring in the holidays with a special tradition that would make even the most warm-blooded of visitors go crazy from the heat— racing to the top of Mount Helios, an active volcano!

added.title: Grey Matter AW2: Lights Out!
added.description: A reliable power supply is vital to the Galvans' around-the-clock research, so when disaster strikes, or more specifically energy-sapping parasites, these brainy beings must have an even more reliable backup plan for keeping the lights on.

added.title: The Might and the Magic
added.description: Seeing Jestro's monster army about to destroy the King's Castle, Aaron rides off to gather his cohorts. In the meantime, the King and Queen bravely go out to defend the city against the monster menace. Is this the end of Knighton?
